<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06344089 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06344089 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Associated Press; Former Pan Am employees line up at assistancecenter in Miami  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  AVIATION; TRAVEL; TRANSPORTATION; SERVICE; COMPANY; BANKRUPT; COURT  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  The nation's large airlines gathered today to scavenge through the remains ofPan American World Airways in a bankruptcy court auction.;   The choice itemson the block were Pan Am's Latin American routes, abandoned last Wednesdaywhen the pioneer of commercial aviation stopped flying after 64 years ofbusiness. United Airlines was considered a top contender.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  COURT STARTS AUCTION OF PAN AM ROUTES  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The courtroom was packed with former Pan Am employees who were angered tosee their carrier die last week after Delta Air Lines at the last minuteremoved a financing package that would have kept Pan Am alive. A number ofthem wore signs that were critical of Delta.;   &quot;Delta . . . they love to lieand it shows,&quot; said one woman's sign.;   Delta said it pulled out of the dealbecause it believed Pan Am's business had fallen off so much there was no wayit could make money.;   But Delta now faces a lawsuit from angry Pan Amcreditors, who filed a lawsuit seeking more than $2.5 billion.;   The suit onFriday charges Delta with failing to deal in good faith and breachingobligations made to Pan Am and its creditors' committee during Delta'snegotiations to buy Pan Am this fall.;   Delta spokesman Neil Monroe saidSunday the airline had expected Pan Am to file suit against it, but wasdisappointed that it had.;   &quot;We feel we had done everything possible to makeit viable for the new Pan Am to be created,&quot; he said. &quot;We reached the pointwhen we decided not to advance them any more money because there was nopossible way the company could survive.&quot;  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  New York  </CITY><EDITION>  Home  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911209  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  December  </MONTH><PG.COL>  13D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  283  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday, December 9, 199100344089,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>